THE Ntuzuma Regional Court has, on 6 July, handed hefty sentences to two hostel murderers. Nkosinathi Mthoko Hlongwane (28) and his co-accused, Nkosinathi Fikani Khumalo (24), were each sentenced to two terms of life imprisonment, after the court heard their of role in killing two people. According to Constable Thenjiswa Ngcobo, on 16 February 2020, two brothers Mjabuliseni (44) and Joseph Mpungose (55) were sitting next to their house on Phumula Road at men’s hostel in KwaMashu when they were ambushed by four men. “The suspects opened fire, fatally wounding the siblings. “Charges of murder were opened at KwaMashu Police Station for investigation,” Ngcobo said in a statement. She said that the detectives followed up on information, which led to the arrest of two accused. The duo made several court appearances until they were sentenced. “Hlongwane was further sentenced to 10 years imprisonment for unlawful possession of a firearm and ammunition,” Ngcobo added.